{
  "info": {
    "name": "Student Path — Auth, User & Bus APIs",
    "description": "## Tokens & scoping (matches dashboard)\n\n| Variable | When to use |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `token` | Default. After **verify-otp**, the test script stores the Sanctum token here. Use for most requests. For **school staff** or **driver** users, list/detail CRUD is limited to that user’s school (driver scope uses `users.school_id` or linked `driver.school_id`). |\n| `admin_token` | **Required** for `POST /api/schools` and `DELETE /api/schools/{id}`. Must be a token for a user with `is_admin: true` (e.g. seed admin, or create token in tinker). **PUT** a school and **GET** list/detail can use a non-admin token when the target is their own school. |\n| `school_id`, `driver_id`, `student_id`, `guardian_id` | Use in path segments for `GET/PUT/DELETE` so you are not hardcoding `1`. Set them from a previous list response. |\n\n## 403 responses\n\nWhen a token is not allowed to act on a resource, the API returns HTTP **403** with body shape:\n\n```json\n{ \"success\": false, \"data\": {}, \"msg\": \"forbidden\" }\n```\n\nor, if the account has no school scope:\n\n```json\n{ \"msg\": \"A school must be linked to this account to perform this action.\" }\n```\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000" },
    { "key": "token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "admin_token", "value": "" },
    { "key": "school_id", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "driver_id", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "student_id", "value": "1" },
    { "key": "guardian_id", "value": "1" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "On **200** from `verify-otp`, the test script stores `data.token` into the collection variable `token` for `Bearer` auth on other folders. For **admin** flows, also paste a Sanctum token from an `is_admin` user into the `admin_token` variable (OTP users are usually not admins).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/send-otp",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"7701234567\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/send-otp"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/verify-otp",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  try {",
                  "    const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "    const t = j.data && (j.data.token || j.data.access_token);",
                  "    if (t) {",
                  "      pm.collectionVariables.set('token', t);",
                  "    }",
                  "  } catch (e) { /* ignore */ }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"7701234567\",\n  \"code\": \"1234\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/verify-otp"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /api/auth/me",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/me"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /api/auth/logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Accept", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{token}}" }
            ],
            "url": "{{base_url}}/api/auth/logout"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
